Isaac Mwaura has been discharged from the hospital after he got injured during a fracas on Tuesday.The Ruiru MP aspirant was in a scuffle with youth allegedly allied to his opponent Simon Kang&rsquo;ara at Kiuu in Githurai.Mwaura was discharged on Wednesday at 8:30am. He is expected to hold a press conference at his residence in Ruiru to address his claims of assassination.The nominated MP posted pictures on Facebook indicating that he had bruised a left ear and the windows of his four-wheel drive vehicle shattered.Reports had earlier indicated that the wound was caused by a bullet after the MP's car was allegedly shot at.But Ruiru OCPD Isaac Thuranira dismissed the claims saying no guns were involved in the incident.Read: MP Mwaura injured during fracas with rival camp in Githurai